My placard had the letters F-B-I written small in the bottom-right corner so as to not arouse suspicion. The agents sniffed me out instantly — true bloodhounds on the hunt for the Guptas — and we walked through OR Tambo International Airport at a brisk pace. “Super,” the agent to my left perked up as we approached the shops. 
               
